  "prompt": "What is stannic hydroxide?",
  "response": "Stannic hydroxide is a chemical compound with the formula Sn(OH)\u2084. It is the hydroxide of stannic (tin in the +4 oxidation state) and is also known as tin(IV) hydroxide. This compound typically appears as a white, amorphous solid and is insoluble in water. Stannic hydroxide can be formed by the reaction of tin(IV) salts with strong bases, such as sodium hydroxide.\n\nStannic hydroxide has various applications, including its use in the preparation of other tin compounds, its role as a pigment in certain applications, and its potential use in catalysis and wastewater treatment. It can also be involved in research settings related to materials science and nanotechnology.",
